01:30:49.350 --> 01:30:51.300
{\an1}how concerned you
are about our finances.

01:30:51.430 --> 01:30:52.820
Mom, will you please
come back inside?

01:30:52.850 --> 01:30:54.760
Oh, my God. Are you kidding me?

01:30:54.890 --> 01:30:57.010
Will you just come
back inside, please?

01:30:57.140 --> 01:30:59.050
They think you're
their son, these people.

01:31:00.100 --> 01:31:01.180
They're not "these people."

01:31:01.220 --> 01:31:02.550
They don't really know you.

01:31:02.680 --> 01:31:04.600
Well, they like
me. They like me.

01:31:04.720 --> 01:31:06.320
I know that that's very
hard for you to believe,

01:31:06.350 --> 01:31:07.720
that they don't think I'm...

01:31:07.850 --> 01:31:09.280
{\an1}you know, that there's
something wrong with me,

01:31:09.310 --> 01:31:10.740
{\an1}that I need to be,
like, fixed, like you do.

01:31:10.760 --> 01:31:12.560
- When have I ever said that?
- Oh, my God.

01:31:12.680 --> 01:31:13.990
{\an1}Mom, I-I have to
go to therapy, right?

01:31:14.010 --> 01:31:15.330
I have to take
drugs. I have to...

01:31:15.390 --> 01:31:16.950
There's-there's
nothing wrong with that.

01:31:17.060 --> 01:31:18.320
There-There's nothing wrong
with needing help, honey.

01:31:18.350 --> 01:31:19.410
Just stop. I know that there is,

01:31:19.430 --> 01:31:20.890
and I know that I'm a burden,

01:31:21.010 --> 01:31:22.490
that I'm the worst thing
that ever happened to you,

01:31:22.510 --> 01:31:23.530
{\an1}and I just... well, I just
ruined your life, okay?!

01:31:23.560 --> 01:31:26.470
No. You are the best thing.

01:31:26.600 --> 01:31:28.810
You're the best thing
that's ever happened to me.

01:31:30.310 --> 01:31:32.310
I'm sorry I can't give you
anything more than that.

01:31:33.720 --> 01:31:35.850
It's not my fault if
other people can.

01:31:43.180 --> 01:31:44.180
I'll see you at home.

01:31:55.640 --> 01:31:57.180
Hi.

01:31:57.310 --> 01:31:59.030
I'm so sorry. I meant
to be there yesterday.

01:31:59.140 --> 01:32:02.310
Okay, well, we have two days
left, and we're $25,000 short.

01:32:02.430 --> 01:32:04.310
Yeah, I just... Everything...

01:32:04.430 --> 01:32:05.930
You're right. I know. I'm sorry.

01:32:06.060 --> 01:32:07.640
Things have been
really busy, so...

01:32:09.980 --> 01:32:11.430
I've been wondering something.

01:32:11.560 --> 01:32:13.310
Mm-hmm?

01:32:14.310 --> 01:32:16.060
Were you ever actually
friends with him?

01:32:17.850 --> 01:32:19.390
What are you talking about?

01:32:19.520 --> 01:32:22.020
Well, the thing about
the emails, it's just that,

01:32:22.140 --> 01:32:23.980
{\an1}like, you and Connor
keep talking about

01:32:24.100 --> 01:32:25.690
climbing this tree
together in June.

01:32:25.810 --> 01:32:26.810
Mm-hmm?

01:32:26.890 --> 01:32:29.100
We were in school in June.

01:32:30.100 --> 01:32:32.270
You didn't have a
cast until September.

01:32:32.390 --> 01:32:34.060
Well, uh, you know what?

01:32:34.190 --> 01:32:36.040
We probably just wrote down
the wrong date or something.

01:32:36.060 --> 01:32:39.480
It's not just the emails, Evan.

01:32:39.600 --> 01:32:41.940
{\an1}You've missed, like,
three meetings in a row.

01:32:42.060 --> 01:32:43.850
If I were his best friend,

01:32:43.980 --> 01:32:45.750
I would be doing everything
I could to make sure

01:32:45.770 --> 01:32:47.370
{\an1}his dream of rebuilding
the orchard came true.

01:32:47.390 --> 01:32:49.020
Okay.

01:32:49.140 --> 01:32:50.870
{\an1}Look, it's terrible that
people aren't giving

01:32:50.890 --> 01:32:52.520
as much money as
we hoped they would.

01:32:52.640 --> 01:32:54.940
It is, but-but it's
not like it's him.

01:32:55.060 --> 01:32:56.310
You know what I mean?

01:32:56.440 --> 01:32:58.350
It's-it's just... it's
an orchard, Alana.

01:32:58.480 --> 01:33:01.100
<font color="#80ffff">♪ ♪</font>

01:33:02.400 --> 01:33:05.400
We have people watching us,

01:33:05.520 --> 01:33:07.730
hoping...

01:33:07.850 --> 01:33:10.850
{\an1}praying that we can
prove Connor wrong.

01:33:10.980 --> 01:33:14.150
{\an1}And if the orchard is
just an empty promise,

01:33:14.270 --> 01:33:17.310
all of those people will
know that Connor was right.

01:33:18.980 --> 01:33:20.440
That no one cares.

01:33:23.480 --> 01:33:25.480
Did you lie to me?

01:33:29.770 --> 01:33:31.860
Did I lie to all these people?

01:33:38.520 --> 01:33:40.360
Just go to your email.

01:33:40.480 --> 01:33:41.730
Another email?

01:33:41.860 --> 01:33:43.820
It's not...

01:33:43.940 --> 01:33:45.980
it's not another email.

01:33:53.900 --> 01:33:56.020
"Dear Evan Hansen..."

01:33:57.980 --> 01:34:00.020
{\an1}If we weren't friends,
then he wouldn't...

01:34:02.020 --> 01:34:04.480
...he wouldn't have
written his note to me.

01:34:07.520 --> 01:34:10.270
{\an1}Look, only his family
have seen this, okay?

01:34:10.400 --> 01:34:14.020
You can't, you can't show
it to anybody else, okay?

01:34:14.150 --> 01:34:15.980
Alana.

01:34:16.110 --> 01:34:17.440
Okay.

01:34:27.110 --> 01:34:28.780
He wasn't right.

01:34:30.150 --> 01:34:31.900
You know that, don't you?

01:34:52.030 --> 01:34:54.570
<font color="#80ffff">♪ The parts we can't
tell, we carry them well ♪</font>

01:34:54.690 --> 01:34:57.280
{\an1}<font color="#80ffff">♪ But that doesn't
mean they're not heavy ♪</font>

